2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] Here's what was designed:
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] **Architecture Decision:** Dual-path implementation — an MVP in the existing Dispatch apparatus (implementable now, no Walker dependency), migrating to Walker-level engine designs when the full rigging system exists. Both paths share the same review criteria and artifact schemas.
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] **Key design answers from the commission questions:**
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 1. **What reviews what?** A clockwork review pass (no LLM) for MVP: uncommitted-changes check always, build/test commands if configured. LLM-as-judge deferred to Phase 3 — too expensive to justify before the mechanical checks are deployed and validated.
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 2. **Where does the loop live?** MVP: inside `dispatch.next()` as a post-session loop. Full design: a `review` clockwork engine + `revise` quick engine grafted into every rig by the origination engine. The Walker traverses both kinds of engines without changes.
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 3. **What does "pass" mean?** Mechanically: no uncommitted changes, build exits clean, tests pass. Each check is cheap, deterministic, and addresses a known failure mode from the commission log.
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 4. **What does a revision look like?** Same worktree, new session. Context: original writ + structured review failure report + `git status` + `git diff HEAD`. Hard cap at 2 retries (3 total sessions).
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 5. **Observatory artifacts:** `review-loop/attempt-N/review.md`, `git-status.txt`, `git-diff.txt` per attempt. Revision sessions tagged with `metadata.trigger: 'review-revision'` for cost accounting. `escalation.md` when budget exhausted.
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 6. **Escalation:** Draft abandoned (inscriptions preserved), writ failed with resolution pointing to artifacts, patron manually reviews before re-dispatching.
2026-04-02T17:40:24Z [anima] 
2026-04-02T17:40:25Z [anima] Six open questions are flagged explicitly for patron review — including default-on vs. opt-in, worktree contamination between attempts, and whether a distinct `revisor` role would outperform using `artificer` with a modified prompt.
